com.samaylabs.optimus.Transport

Class StateMachineAgv

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samaylabs.optimus.Transport.StateMachineAgv

  • public class StateMachineAgv
extends java.lang.Object
    This class holds the logic based on which behaviour of agv is controlled from server. It has execute method which switches between states and changes the behaviour of its respected agv.
    Author:
    Tulve Shabab Kasim

      • execute

        public void execute()
        This method contains a switch case which alters the behaviour of agv, Each case has its own set of conditions. To properlt start this agv Constructor should be properly initilized without any null values.

      • agvMover

        public void agvMover()
        This method is to specifically for Movement of agv, it iterates throughout the current path assigned to statemachine until some break conditions are satisfies. Breakes if: Abor is true made by scheduler, UI abort done from userInterface, If agv takes wrong path.
